cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language inference, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed model uses a tree-based convolutional neural network (TBCNN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves heuristic matching layers, which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
